A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 3 of Chapter 13 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to excise tax on rooms, lodgings, and accommodations, so as to change certain
3 definitions regarding such taxes; to provide an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and
4 for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 3 of Chapter 13 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 excise tax on rooms, lodgings, and accommodations, is amended in Code Section 48-13-50.2,
9 relating to definitions regarding such taxes, by revising paragraph (2) as follows:
10 "(2) 'Innkeeper' means any person who is subject to taxation under this article for the
11 furnishing for value to the public any rooms, lodgings, or accommodations."
12 SECTION 2.
13 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
14 without such approval.
